meanings.definition: Carl August von Steinheil (1801–1870), a German physicist, astronomer, and inventor.
meanings.english_definition: Carl August von Steinheil (1801–1870), a German physicist, astronomer, and inventor.

meanings.definition: Hugo Adolf Steinheil (1832–1893), a German astronomer and instrument maker, son of Carl August von Steinheil.
meanings.english_definition: Hugo Adolf Steinheil (1832–1893), a German astronomer and instrument maker, son of Carl August von Steinheil.

etymology.value: From German Stein 'stone' + Heil 'hail, greeting, salvation, well-being, luck'.
